    {
        "content": "<p>I wonder if a configuration option is missing ...</p>",
        "id": 526762413,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1751449918
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, sorry for the missing part. Here is my config</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>cat<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">&lt;&lt;EOF &gt;linux/kernel/configs/rfl-for-rust-ci.config</span>\n<span class=\"s\"># CONFIG_WERROR is not set</span>\n\n<span class=\"s\">CONFIG_RUST=y</span>\n\n<span class=\"s\">CONFIG_SAMPLES=y</span>\n<span class=\"s\">CONFIG_SAMPLES_RUST=y</span>\n\n<span class=\"s\">CONFIG_SAMPLE_RUST_MINIMAL=y</span>\n<span class=\"s\">CONFIG_SAMPLE_RUST_PRINT=y</span>\n\n<span class=\"s\">CONFIG_RUST_PHYLIB_ABSTRACTIONS=y</span>\n<span class=\"s\">CONFIG_AX88796B_PHY=y</span>\n<span class=\"s\">CONFIG_AX88796B_RUST_PHY=y</span>\n\n<span class=\"s\">CONFIG_KUNIT=y</span>\n<span class=\"s\">CONFIG_RUST_KERNEL_DOCTESTS=y</span>\n<span class=\"s\">EOF</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 526762522,
        "sender_full_name": "Vague",
        "timestamp": 1751449956
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What happens if you add <code>CONFIG_TRACEPOINTS</code>?</p>",
        "id": 526762871,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1751450067
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Bad luck... It didn't work...</p>",
        "id": 526763374,
        "sender_full_name": "Vague",
        "timestamp": 1751450223
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I wonder how rfl CI in Rust lang repo can pass, because these configs are stolen from <a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/f51c9870bab634afb9e7a262b6ca7816bb9e940d/src/ci/docker/scripts/rfl-build.sh#L65\">there</a>.</p>",
        "id": 526763889,
        "sender_full_name": "Vague",
        "timestamp": 1751450382
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The only difference is I'm running the build at a slightly old commit back in a few weeks.</p>",
        "id": 526764231,
        "sender_full_name": "Vague",
        "timestamp": 1751450474
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I also noticed this warning:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"o\">***</span>\n<span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Rust</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">generator</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">bindgen</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">0.69.5</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">together</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">libclang</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&gt;=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">19.1</span>\n<span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">may</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">work</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">due</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bug</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">https</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"c1\">//github.com/rust-lang/rust-bindgen/pull/2824),</span>\n<span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unless</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">patched</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">like</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Debian</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">s</span><span class=\"p\">).</span>\n<span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"n\">Your</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindgen</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">version</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"mf\">0.65.1</span>\n<span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"n\">Your</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">libclang</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">version</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">20.1.7</span>\n<span class=\"o\">***</span>\n<span class=\"o\">***</span>\n<span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Please</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">see</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Documentation</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">quick</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">start</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rst</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">details</span>\n<span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">on</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">how</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">up</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Rust</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">support</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n<span class=\"o\">***</span>\n<span class=\"n\">Rust</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">available</span><span class=\"o\">!</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Is it normal?</p>",
        "id": 526764517,
        "sender_full_name": "Vague",
        "timestamp": 1751450566
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, that's the warning for exactly the bug that breaks tracepoints.</p>",
        "id": 526768110,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1751451786
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I suggest you update bindgen so that you have a working version.</p>",
        "id": 526768208,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1751451817
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Alright.</p>\n<p>But <code>bindgen version:  0.65.1</code> is from <a href=\"https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/blob/769e324b66b0d92d04f315d0c45a0f72737c7494/scripts/min-tool-version.sh#L39\">linux/scripts/min-tool-version.sh</a>.</p>",
        "id": 526769449,
        "sender_full_name": "Vague",
        "timestamp": 1751452274
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I've installed the latest v0.72.0, the warning is gone, but still get the compilation error.</p>",
        "id": 526770414,
        "sender_full_name": "Vague",
        "timestamp": 1751452589
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If you just changed the bindgen version, then clean output files and compile again.</p>",
        "id": 526770522,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1751452627
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Wow, it works after the clean.</p>\n<p>I'm grateful for your instant help! <span aria-label=\"octopus\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f419\" role=\"img\" title=\"octopus\">:octopus:</span></p>",
        "id": 526771394,
        "sender_full_name": "Vague",
        "timestamp": 1751452932
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"931980\">Vague</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/291565-Help/topic/cannot.20find.20value.20.60__tracepoint_rust_sample_loaded.60.20in.20crate/near/526769449\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Alright.</p>\n<p>But <code>bindgen version:  0.65.1</code> is from <a href=\"https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/blob/769e324b66b0d92d04f315d0c45a0f72737c7494/scripts/min-tool-version.sh#L39\">linux/scripts/min-tool-version.sh</a>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The versions listed in min-tool-version are not always sufficient. It lists the versions that are required in all cases, but some kernel configurations require higher version numbers.</p>",
        "id": 526771400,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1751452934
    },
