    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"931980\">Vague</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/291565-Help/topic/.E2.9C.94.20cannot.20find.20value.20.60__tracepoint_rust_sample_loaded.60.20in.20.2E.2E.2E/near/526769449\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>But <code>bindgen version:  0.65.1</code> is from <a href=\"https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/blob/769e324b66b0d92d04f315d0c45a0f72737c7494/scripts/min-tool-version.sh#L39\">linux/scripts/min-tool-version.sh</a>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yes, but as the message says, certain combinations do not work: \"<code>together with libclang &gt;= 19.1</code>\"</p>",
